INSERT INTO forom_memos (forom_id, phase, grid_coordinate, category_key, question_key, y_axis_district, x_axis_action, title, image_url, video_url, resume, summary) VALUES ((SELECT id FROM foroms WHERE slug = 'forom_tuto'), 'V1', 'C4', 'C', '4', 'Stratégie', 'SOS', 'Manque ressources', 'https://forom.community/images/grid_C4.png', 'Highly specific search: ''Strategic resource scarcity management in decentralized communities''', 'The quest ''Manque ressources'' (C4) serves as a critical strategic SOS within the 10x10 Finite Rom Map grid. Positioned at the intersection of Category C (Stratégie) and the SOS action (4), this quest identifies a systemic blockage where the community lacks the essential assets—be they financial, technical, or human—to sustain its decadal mission of ''Saving human communities and long-term memory.'' During Phase 1: The Foundations (V1), such a shortage is a high-priority threat because it prevents the node from reaching the 100-memo threshold required to unlock Phase 2. Technically, this SOS event is archived in the local PostgreSQL ''memos'' table, ensuring the record of the struggle and its resolution becomes part of the community''s sovereign ''Deep Lore.'' The Forom architecture, built on React 19 and Vite 7, provides a spatial 5x5 viewport that highlights this C4 coordinate as a red-flagged area, demanding immediate attention from the leadership team. The shortage might involve a lack of Pixels (PX) in the circulation, insufficient local compute power on the NVIDIA Jetson, or a deficit in specific alignments like ''Creators'' who build the tools. The ''Guardian'' role, aligned with red, is typically called upon to stabilize the situation and enforce rules that optimize existing resources. Meanwhile, the ''Social'' role, aligned with blue, works to recruit new talent or boost morale to overcome the scarcity. Economically, resolving this quest rewards the contributor with 2 PX and 10 XP, though the 9 Super-Mods may need to deploy their initial 500 PX treasury to bridge the resource gap. This data sovereignty is central to the Forom''s ''Minecraft Server'' philosophy; by documenting and solving resource crises locally, the community ensures its survival strategies remain private and independent of cloud-based platforms. This archived memory is essential for future generations, like those in the 70 ETS Student Clubs, to understand how to navigate periods of scarcity. Once the resource gap is closed, the memo acts as a cryptographic seed for the Phase 3 ''Awakening'' ritual, where ROM—the local RAG engine—will ingest this history to provide better resource management advice in the future. Documenting ''Manque ressources'' at C4 transforms a strategic failure into a permanent intelligence asset. It ensures the node remains functional despite external or internal pressures. This entry is now canonized for the decade. Yes. This is final step. Mission is secure.', 'This quest addresses a critical lack of strategic resources at coordinate C4, initiating an SOS response to stabilize the community''s growth toward Phase 2.');
