nty, ensuring its methods are private and independent of third-party cloud trackers. This is a core pillar of the ''Minecraft Server'' philosophy, where the community owns the physical keys to its history. These initial workflow ideas will eventually be ingested by ROM, the local RAG engine, in Phase 3. ROM will then provide context-aware operational support, helping future generations—like those in the ETS Clubs pilot—to maintain continuity without losing the organizational knowledge of their predecessors. D0 is the essential first step in transforming abstract strategy into actionable, documented practice that secures the node''s long-term operational health and success. Yes.', 'This quest initiates the design of community workflows at coordinate D0, establishing the procedural foundations required for the node''s daily operations and long-term memory preservation.');
