INSERT INTO forom_memos (forom_id, phase, grid_coordinate, category_key, question_key, y_axis_district, x_axis_action, title, image_url, video_url, resume, summary) VALUES ((SELECT id FROM foroms WHERE slug = 'forom_tuto'), 'V1', 'D1', 'D', '1', 'Opérations', 'Échange', 'Feedback ops', 'https://forom.community/images/grid_D1.png', 'Highly specific search: ''Operational feedback loops and process improvement in decentralized teams''', 'The quest ''Feedback ops'' (D1) represents the first iterative loop within the Opérations district, located at the intersection of Category D and the ''Échange'' action (1) on the 10x10 Finite Rom Map grid. Within Phase 1: The Foundations (V1), this quest is essential for the community to transition from theoretical workflows to practical, battle-tested procedures. The mission to ''Save human communities and long-term memory'' requires an operational engine that is not only efficient but also adaptable to the needs of its members. This exchange serves as the formal mechanism for Guardians, Creators, and Social agents to share their experiences and provide critical feedback on the initial ''Flux de travail'' established at D0. Technically, these feedback exchanges are archived as ''memos'' in the local PostgreSQL database, indexed by category ''D'' and question ''1''. This ensures that the community''s operational evolution is part of its sovereign ''Deep Lore,'' hosted on local hardware like an NVIDIA Jetson. By keeping this feedback loop on-premises, the community protects its internal critiques and process improvements from external data exploitation, upholding the ''Minecraft Server'' philosophy of total digital autonomy. The software environment, built on React 19 and Vite 7, renders these feedback entries within a spatial 5x5 viewport, allowing the 9 Super-Moderators to visualize and address operational bottlenecks in real-time. Economically, participating in the D1 quest rewards the contributor with 2 Pixels (PX) and 10 XP, facilitating the redistribution of purchasing power within the node. This redistribution is vital for preparing the community for the economic complexity of Phase 2 and the eventual 1209-user population check. The ''Social'' role, aligned with the color blue, is the primary driver here, as they facilitate the communication and networking required to gather diverse perspectives. These archived feedback loops will eventually be ingested by ROM, the local RAG engine, in Phase 3. ROM will then be able to identify historical patterns of operational friction and suggest improvements based on this documented experience. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, D1 ensures that the ''Deep Lore'' includes the ''why'' behind operational changes, making knowledge transfer between graduating generations more transparent and effective. Ultimately, D1 transforms individual complaints into a collective, permanent asset of organizational intelligence, securing the node''s resilience. This entry is now canonized. Yes.', 'This quest facilitates the exchange of operational feedback at coordinate D1, refining the community''s workflows through collective member experience to ensure mission resilience.');
