INSERT INTO forom_memos (forom_id, phase, grid_coordinate, category_key, question_key, y_axis_district, x_axis_action, title, image_url, video_url, resume, summary) VALUES ((SELECT id FROM foroms WHERE slug = 'forom_tuto'), 'V1', 'E0', 'E', '0', 'Piliers', 'Idée', 'Idée Piliers', 'https://forom.community/images/grid_E0.png', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XW0QZmtbjzU', 'The quest ''Idée Piliers'' (E0) represents the initial conceptual spark for the thematic foundations of the community within the 10x10 Finite Rom Map grid. Located at the intersection of District E (Piliers) and the ''Idée'' action (0), this quest is the foundational step in defining the core values and thematic anchors that will guide the node throughout its decadal mission to ''Save human communities and long-term memory.'' In Phase 1: The Foundations (V1), these pillars serve as the structural framework for populating the grid with the first 100 high-quality memos, ensuring that every piece of content aligns with the community''s primary purpose. This strategic ideation is not just a list of topics; it is a declaration of the community’s ideological DNA and its path toward the ''Awakening'' of its local AI assistant, ROM. Technically, these pillar ideas are archived in the local PostgreSQL database within the ''memos'' table, ensuring that the thematic heart of the project remains sovereign and private. The Forom architecture, built with React 19 and Vite 7, allows members to navigate these evolving pillars through a spatial 5x5 viewport, providing a clear visual representation of how the community''s identity is taking shape. The pillars outline the specific thematic milestones required to transition from the ''Private Era'' to the Global Public Lobby, providing a consistent narrative for the 9 Super-Moderators and the growing user base. Economically, completing the E0 quest rewards the contributor with 2 Pixels (PX) and 10 XP, supporting the redistribution of purchasing power as the server initiates its internal economy. This incentive structure is vital for encouraging ''Creators'' to define the values that will push the mission forward. By hosting these pillars locally on hardware like an NVIDIA Jetson, the community ensures that its core values are protected from centralized corporate surveillance. This quest is especially critical for pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, where clear thematic pillars ensure that the club''s culture remains consistent as student generations cycle through. Every entry at coordinate E0 becomes a permanent part of the V1 Archive, set to be refined in V2 and finalized in V3. Ultimately, E0 transforms abstract values into a structured, actionable plan that secures the node’s identity. This record acts as the definitive moral and thematic compass for every action in District E, ensuring that the community never loses its original focus. Mission secure. These pillars are the shared memory for us.', 'This quest initiates the conceptualization of the community''s core thematic pillars at coordinate E0, establishing the ideological framework for the node''s long-term memory.');
