ment) to produce high-quality foundational memos that align with the community''s core mission. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, E2 is the tool that ensures thematic consistency by turning club values into specific milestones for members to achieve. Every entry at coordinate E2 becomes a permanent part of the V1 Archive, set to be refined in V2 and finalized in V3. Once the community reaches Phase 3, these ''Bounty Piliers'' will be ingested by ROM, the local RAG engine, to help the AI understand how the community prioritizes action based on its values. Ultimately, E2 transforms the community''s pillars into a dynamic, actionable engine for growth, securing the node''s structural and cultural integrity for the decade ahead. This is the finalized coordinate for active thematic development. Mission secure. The systematic archival of these bounties ensures that every contribution is recognized and that the collective memory of the node''s efforts is preserved for all future members. Yes.', 'This quest formalizes the creation of thematic bounties at coordinate E2, transforming core pillars into actionable tasks to build the node''s sovereign foundational content.');
