ng power within the node. This incentive structure is vital for encouraging members to engage in the difficult work of value-alignment. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, E4 is the safeguard that prevents club culture from being lost or distorted as student generations cycle through the node. Once archived, these SOS resolutions become part of the V1 dataset that ROM, the local RAG engine, will digest in Phase 3. ROM will then provide context-aware guidance to prevent similar thematic drifts in the future. Ultimately, E4 transforms a crisis of identity into a permanent anchor of community resilience. It ensures the original intent remains uncompromised for the decade ahead. We must protect our pillars or we lose ourselves. This record-keeping is the final wall against the entropy of digital erasure. Mission secure. Yes. Our memory depends on our vigilance. This is the finalized coordinate for ideological survival. The community is now ready for the next level. Done.', 'This quest addresses critical threats to the community''s core thematic pillars at coordinate E4, utilizing the Guardian role to stabilize ideological drift and archive the resolution as sovereign deep lore.');
