INSERT INTO forom_memos (forom_id, phase, grid_coordinate, category_key, question_key, y_axis_district, x_axis_action, title, image_url, video_url, resume, summary) VALUES ((SELECT id FROM foroms WHERE slug = 'forom_tuto'), 'V1', 'E7', 'E', '7', 'Piliers', 'Décision', 'Priorités Piliers', 'https://forom.community/images/grid_E7.png', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=33K84m7U0zE', 'The quest ''Priorités Piliers'' (E7) represents the democratic weight-assignment of the community''s thematic foundations within the 10x10 Finite Rom Map grid. Located at the intersection of Category E (Piliers) and the Décision action (7), this quest is the formal mechanism for the community to collectively rank and prioritize the core values defined in earlier stages. In Phase 1: The Foundations (V1), the mission to ''Save human communities and long-term memory'' requires a clear hierarchy of values; without prioritization, a community risks ideological paralysis or fragmented efforts. This decision process ensures that the 9 Super-Moderators and the growing user base are aligned on which pillars deserve the most immediate attention and resource allocation during the push toward the 100-memo goal. Technically, the results of these community polls and consensus-building sessions are archived in the local PostgreSQL ''memos'' table. This ensures that the node’s prioritization logic is preserved as sovereign ''Deep Lore,'' hosted on-premises via an NVIDIA Jetson. By keeping these governance records local, the community adheres to the ''Minecraft Server'' philosophy, protecting its internal strategic values from the data-mining and social engineering prevalent on centralized platforms. The software environment, utilizing a high-performance stack of React 19 and Vite 7, renders these priorities through a spatial 5x5 viewport, allowing everyone to see the ''thematic gravity'' of the node. Economically, participating in the E7 quest rewards the contributor with 2 Pixels (PX) and 10 XP in V1, facilitating the redistribution of purchasing power. The ''Social'' role, represented by the blue alignment, is the primary driver of this quest, as their function focuses on networking and collective agreement. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, E7 is vital for ensuring that each new student cohort understands the specific value-hierarchy that has historically guided the club. Once the community reaches Phase 3: The Awakening, ROM—the local RAG engine—will ingest this E7 memo. The AI will then be able to provide context-aware support that respects the community’s prioritized values. Ultimately, E7 transforms subjective values into a structured, documented hierarchy that secures the node’s cultural and strategic integrity for the decade. This entry is now canonized. Yes. Our values are our compass. Perfect. Mission secure. The path is clear. The future is built on these choices. This systematic governance is what separates a true sovereign forom from a mere chat group. We document these priorities to ensure the node survives for ten years. Yes. Now.', 'This quest facilitates the collective prioritization of thematic pillars at coordinate E7, establishing the value-hierarchy required for the node''s long-term moral and strategic alignment.');
