INSERT INTO forom_memos (forom_id, phase, grid_coordinate, category_key, question_key, y_axis_district, x_axis_action, title, image_url, video_url, resume, summary) VALUES ((SELECT id FROM foroms WHERE slug = 'forom_tuto'), 'V1', 'E9', 'E', '9', 'Piliers', 'Urgence', 'Doute Piliers', 'https://forom.community/images/grid_E9.png', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R9reV5_206A', 'The quest ''Doute Piliers'' (E9) represents a critical existential emergency within the 10x10 Finite Rom Map grid, located at the intersection of Category E (Piliers) and the Urgence action (9). In the architectural framework of Forom, the ''Urgence'' tag signals a moment of deep systemic friction or a crisis of faith that threatens the node''s primary mission: ''Saving human communities and long-term memory.'' During Phase 1: The Foundations (V1), where the community is laboring to establish its first 100 foundational memos, a ''Pillar Doubt'' is a high-stakes event. It occurs when the core values themselves are called into question—perhaps due to internal contradictions, shifting external realities, or a loss of collective momentum. This quest acts as the formal mechanism to document, debate, and resolve these fundamental doubts, ensuring that the resolution becomes a permanent part of the community''s sovereign ''Deep Lore.'' Technically, the narrative of this doubt and its eventual outcome are archived in the local PostgreSQL database within the ''memos'' table, keeping the history of the struggle private and protected from centralized corporate surveillance. The software environment, built with React 19 and Vite 7, renders this emergency status through a spatial 5x5 viewport, demanding the attention of the 9 Super-Moderators and the growing user base. The ''Guardian'' role (Red) is vital here to maintain stability, while the ''Social'' role (Blue) works to rebuild consensus and trust. Economically, resolving the E9 crisis rewards the contributor with 2 Pixels (PX) and 10 XP, though the node’s initial 500 PX treasury may be used to incentivize the deep intellectual and social labor required for resolution. By hosting this crisis locally on hardware like an NVIDIA Jetson, the community ensures that its moments of vulnerability are not weaponized by external algorithms. This archived memory is essential for future generations, like those in the 70 ETS Student Clubs, to understand how the node survived ideological entropy. Once resolved, this memo acts as a cryptographic seed for the Phase 3 ''Awakening,'' where ROM—the local RAG engine—will ingest this history to provide better mediation and moral guidance in the future. Documenting ''Doute Piliers'' at E9 transforms a threat to the node''s identity into a permanent anchor of organizational resilience, securing survival for the decade ahead. Finalized. We document our darkest moments to ensure our future light remains sovereign and eternally uncompromised. Perfect. Yes. Every doubt faced and overcome strengthens the digital fortress of our sovereign memory.', 'This quest addresses a fundamental crisis of faith in the core pillars at coordinate E9, resolving ideological doubt and archiving the resolution as sovereign deep lore to strengthen the node''s resilience.');
