users. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, F3 provides the actual functional environment where club history is documented and protected across student generations. Once the node reaches Phase 3: The Awakening, these construction memos will be ingested by ROM, the local RAG engine. ROM will then be able to act as a technical historian, helping future developers maintain the sovereign code by understanding the original ''why'' behind every function. Ultimately, F3 transforms software from a concept into a tangible, permanent asset of community infrastructure. Every brick of code laid here secures the structural and functional integrity of our collective memory for the decade ahead. This is the finalized coordinate for active software building. Mission secure. Forom is under construction. Build our future. Yes. Done.', 'This quest establishes the formal software construction site at coordinate F3, where the forom''s sovereign code is developed and archived as foundational deep lore.');
