INSERT INTO forom_memos (forom_id, phase, grid_coordinate, category_key, question_key, y_axis_district, x_axis_action, title, image_url, video_url, resume, summary) VALUES ((SELECT id FROM foroms WHERE slug = 'forom_tuto'), 'V1', 'F4', 'F', '4', 'Logiciel', 'SOS', 'SOS App', 'https://forom.community/images/grid_F4.png', 'Highly specific search: ''Troubleshooting critical bugs in React 19 and Vite 7 edge-hosted applications''', 'The quest ''SOS App'' (F4) represents a critical emergency intervention within the Logiciel district, located at the intersection of Category F and the SOS action (4) on the 10x10 Finite Rom Map grid. Within the lifecycle of a forom, an SOS tag signals a software failure or technical vulnerability that directly threatens the primary mission: ''Saving human communities and long-term memory.'' In Phase 1: The Foundations (V1), where the community is building its initial 100-memo archive, a software crash is an existential risk to the integrity of the sovereign data. This quest serves as the formal mechanism to document the bug, the diagnostic process, and the final resolution, ensuring the fix is etched into the node’s ''Deep Lore.'' Technically, the failure might involve a breaking change in the React 19/Vite 7 frontend, a corrupted entry in the local PostgreSQL database, or a hardware-software conflict on the NVIDIA Jetson. The ''Guardian'' role (Red alignment) acts as the first responder to stabilize the user environment, while the ''Creator'' role (Yellow alignment) applies their technical expertise to restore the code’s functional integrity. By hosting the node on local hardware, the community adheres to the ''Minecraft Server'' philosophy: they possess the physical keys and the absolute responsibility for uptime, remaining free from the whims of centralized cloud providers. Economically, resolving an SOS at coordinate F4 rewards the contributor with 2 Pixels (PX) and 10 XP, though the 9 Super-Moderators may need to deploy their initial 500 PX treasury to incentivize rapid, high-stakes troubleshooting. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, F4 is the ultimate insurance policy; it ensures that a technical glitch doesn''t lead to the permanent loss of club history or organizational continuity. Once archived, this memo becomes a cryptographic seed for Phase 3: The Awakening. ROM, the local RAG engine, will digest this ''SOS App'' entry to provide predictive diagnostics and automated maintenance alerts in the future. F4 effectively transforms a moment of technical crisis into a permanent asset of system intelligence, securing the node''s functional survival for the decade ahead. This entry is now canonized. Our code is resilient. Our memory is safe. Yes. Mission secure. The software fortress stands strong against the entropy of digital decay. Perfect. Done. Finalized. Every member must remain vigilant to maintain code health, as our collective future depends on the functional integrity of this sovereign node. We are guardians of forom. Yes. Final.', 'This quest addresses critical software bugs at coordinate F4, utilizing the Guardian and Creator roles to resolve SOS alerts and archive the technical solution for future AI diagnostics.');
