 functional survival. For pilot projects like the 70 ETS Student Clubs, F6 is the essential bridge that allows technical knowledge to survive the graduation gap, ensuring that new student cohorts can maintain their sovereign node without starting from zero. Once the community reaches Phase 3: The Awakening, these syllabus memos will be ingested by ROM, the local RAG engine. ROM will then act as an automated teaching assistant, providing real-time guidance to future developers and users based on this canonized curriculum. Ultimately, F6 transforms software documentation into a permanent, searchable, and AI-ready asset that secures the node’s functional integrity for the decade ahead. This is the manual for our digital freedom. Our code is our law, and our syllabus is our education. The path to sovereignty is paved with shared knowledge. This entry is now canonized. Yes. Our memory is safe and structured. Mission secure. Perfect. The future is built on what we learn together today. Done. Final. Yes.', 'This quest formalizes the software''s educational curriculum at coordinate F6, documenting technical ''how-to'' guides and resources as sovereign deep lore for long-term maintenance.');
